integration, the session-lane message queueing, the orchestrator/operator
agent, and the memory and proactive-suggestion subsystems, together with the
web/desktop application scaffold.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTICE OF MODIFICATIONS (Apache License 2.0, Section 4(b))
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository has been modified and substantially extended beyond the
KIRA-Slack base. Notable additions include:

  * AICC — a real-time voice/telephony assistant (streaming voice response)
    with an asynchronous post-call pipeline (recording, transcription,
    classification, notification).
  * Agent Factory — template-based, human-in-the-loop-gated self-extension
    for generating and loading new domain sub-agents at runtime.
  * An MCP server exposing the platform as a tool endpoint, with OAuth 2.1
    (PKCE / DCR) authentication.
  * Sub-agent delegation (call_sub_agent) and additional domain/tool
    integrations (e.g. CRM and other connectors).

